      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OHTANI FORCE (2) was never in contention last time after losing his position early at Capalaba, but prior to that won by 2.25 lengths at Q Straight (19.35) beating Eliza Day in a Grade 6 on July 9. Can make amends. ETERNITY BRIDGE (1) could manage only seventh after copping a check in the run last time in a Grade 5 at this track, finishing 40 lengths from the winner (33.29). Should be in this for a long way. NOT HALF BAD (8) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fourth (25.68) in a Grade 5 at Grafton. Solid record at the distance winning two races. The form out of last run is most impressive. Expected to feature in the finish. TO XIBALBA (7) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
